    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Governing equations and constitutive models (turbulence closure, hemolysis power-law model) are appropriate for the flow regime and validated against independent data.",
      "rationale": "A comprehensive qualitative assessment of model form adequacy was conducted by the simulation team and an independent domain expert in blood pump fluid mechanics. The SST k-omega turbulence model was selected based on its established performance for rotating machinery with adverse pressure gradients, as documented in multiple peer-reviewed publications for similar centrifugal pump geometries. The Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model is the accepted standard for CFD-based hemolysis prediction in regulatory submissions. Model form choices are consistent with FDA-recognized simulation practices for cardiovascular devices. The expert panel concluded that the selected model forms are appropriate for the COU operating envelope and device geometry, providing sufficient confidence for the MRL 2 assessment without requiring formal level quantification beyond this structured qualitative review."
    },
