    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment for COU1 (CPB hemolysis prediction at MRL 2) is Accepted. Seven of thirteen credibility factors were formally assessed; all seven meet or exceed their required levels. The remaining six factors are not assessed, which is acceptable at Model Risk Level 2 per ASME V&V 40. Validation evidence demonstrates quantitative agreement between CFD predictions and experimental hemolysis measurements within 15% across all five operating points. The model is judged sufficiently credible to support identification of worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device.",
